# MVP Experiment Result

## 1. Usability Testing Results

The Smart Campus Event Hub prototype was tested with students from Rangsit University to evaluate whether users could discover campus events, search activities, view event details, register for events, and understand the main features of the platform.

| Tester Code | Task ID | Task Description | Completed | Time (seconds) | Help Needed | Confusion Point | Rating Clarity (1-5) | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---:|---|---|---:|---|
| T01 | T1 | Understand homepage purpose | Yes | 30 | No | - | 5 | Homepage clearly explains the purpose of finding and joining campus events. |
| T01 | T2 | Find an upcoming campus event | Yes | 55 | No | - | 5 | Event list was easy to understand and displayed useful information. |
| T02 | T3 | Search for an event using category or keyword filter | Yes | 70 | No | Unsure which category filter to choose | 4 | Filter labels should be more specific and easier to understand. |
| T02 | T4 | Open event details page | Yes | 45 | No | - | 4 | Event information was clear, but users wanted more visual details. |
| T03 | T5 | Register for a selected event | Yes | 85 | No | Registration button was slightly difficult to find | 4 | Make the registration button more noticeable. |
| T04 | T6 | View upcoming events in dashboard/calendar | Yes | 60 | No | - | 5 | Calendar view helped users track upcoming activities. |
| T05 | T7 | Check event reminder notification feature | No | 90 | Yes | Unclear how reminders are activated | 3 | Need clearer explanation of reminder settings. |
| T05 | T8 | Submit an event through organizer page | Yes | 100 | No | Required fields were not obvious | 4 | Add clearer instructions for organizers. |

