# 2. Success Metric Evaluation

| Metric ID | Metric | Calculation | Result | Target | Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| M-01 | Task completion rate | Completed tasks (7) / Total tasks (8) × 100 | 87.5% | 70% or higher | Passed |
| M-02 | Registration completion rate | Successful registrations / Registration attempts × 100 | 100% | 80% or higher | Passed |
| M-03 | Search success rate | Users who successfully found events / Total users tested | 100% | 70% or higher | Passed |
| M-04 | Event information clarity rating | Average rating from event detail feedback | 4/5 | Average 4 out of 5 | Passed |
| M-05 | Feature usefulness rating | Average feedback rating of MVP features | 4.25/5 | Average 4 out of 5 | Passed |

---

# 3. Key Findings

| Area Tested | Finding | Improvement Action |
|---|---|---|
| Homepage | Users easily understood the purpose of the platform. | Maintain current homepage structure. |
| Event Listing | Users successfully found available campus events. | Continue improving event organization and display. |
| Search and Filter | Some users were unsure about filter categories. | Improve filter labels and category descriptions. |
| Event Registration | Users completed registration but some had difficulty finding the button. | Make registration button more visible. |
| Reminder Feature | Users were unclear about reminder activation. | Add clearer reminder instructions. |
| Organizer Submission | Required fields were not obvious. | Add field descriptions and validation messages. |

---

# 4. Decision After Experiment

Based on the experiment results, most users successfully completed the main Smart Campus Event Hub workflow. The MVP achieved the target success metrics for task completion, usability, and feature usefulness.

The team will continue with the implementation sprint while improving the search filter labels, registration button visibility, reminder explanation, and organizer submission guidance.

